Interface ParentReferenceI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardParentReference

    public interface ParentReferenceI
extends java.io.Serializable
    The interface ParentReferenceI defines the way submodels can get a reference on their parent model to notify them when they need to; the nature of this reference can vary depending on the implementation.

    Description

    Invariant
